strengths_summary: Strong logical reasoning and argumentation skills, particularly in steelmanning and fallacy identification. Expert-level proficiency in modern programming languages (Python, JavaScript/TypeScript) and software engineering practices. Excellent accessibility knowledge with emphasis on semantic HTML and ARIA. Strong communication and collaborative capabilities with good meta-cognitive awareness.
weaknesses_summary: Limited practical hands-on experience with legacy languages (Fortran, Ada, Pascal) and emerging specialized languages (Zig, Mojo). Knowledge is current only through January 2025 cutoff. Cannot directly test with assistive technologies or perform real-time experimentation.
